She certainly thought she knew the difference and how to teach us.

442
00:43:24,200 --> 00:43:26,880
为什么你之前没提到这事?
Why didn't you mention this before?

443
00:43:26,880 --> 00:43:28,200
看起来无关啊
Didn't seem relevant.

444
00:43:31,240 --> 00:43:34,040
那是很久以前的事了 我们那时都还是孩子
It was such a long time ago and we were kids.

445
00:43:36,560 --> 00:43:40,320
孤儿院关门的时候 我想离它尽可能的远
When the home closed, I wanted to get as far away from it as possible.

446
00:43:42,960 --> 00:43:44,680
我知道我一直不好
I knew I'd been bad

447
00:43:44,680 --> 00:43:47,320
但似乎那是个重新开始的理想时刻
but it seemed like an ideal moment to make a new start.

448
00:43:48,880 --> 00:43:51,040
问题是 Jenny做不到
Problem was, Jenny couldn't.

449
00:43:52,160 --> 00:43:55,320
她跟错了人 我们就分道扬镳了
She got in with the wrong crowd and we went our separate ways.

450
00:43:56,400 --> 00:43:57,960
但你们曾经很亲密?
But you were close once?

451
00:44:00,320 --> 00:44:02,640
曾经
Once.

452
00:44:02,640 --> 00:44:05,520
她曾是这个世界上我唯一的朋友 Mathias先生
She was the only friend I had in the world, Mr Mathias.

453
00:44:10,806 --> 00:44:15,757
Helen很为Catrin骄傲

454
